# My Biggest Strategic Advice

Ivan, after following this project from its earliest ideas to what it has become today, I think there is one principle that should guide every remaining decision.

**Don't try to demonstrate everything byDebut will become. Demonstrate one experience so compelling that the judges immediately believe the rest is inevitable.**

The architecture we've created is your competitive foundation. The MVP is simply the smallest window through which the judges can clearly see that future.

---

# I recommend one final strategic shift

From this point forward, I would stop thinking in terms of **features**.

Instead, organize every sprint around **moments**.

For the XPRIZE MVP, there are only **seven moments that matter**:

1. **Finish the book.**
2. **Scan the QR code.**
3. **Enter the Story Portal.**
4. **Watch Gemini understand the story.**
5. **Create a new Story Lineage.**
6. **Publish it into the Living Story Universe.**
7. **See the universe evolve instantly.**

If those seven moments are beautiful, fast, emotionally engaging, and technically solid, I believe you will have created a demonstration that is not just memorable—it will clearly communicate why byDebut exists and why Gemini is essential to making it possible. I would make every line of code, every UI decision, and every AI workflow serve one of those seven moments.
